# TypeScript under `projects/`

- Prefer explicit types on exported functions and public class methods.
- Validate external input at HTTP boundaries (Zod in token-safety-bot; Joi where already used in token-sniper-bot).
- Use `Array<T>` in new code if the surrounding file already does; otherwise match the file’s existing array style.
- Handle errors with clear messages; avoid empty `catch` blocks except where intentionally swallowing optional failures (e.g. broadcast to one chat).
